A diastasis recti is the widening of the gap between the rectus abdominis muscles (6 pack muscle). The muscles naturally separate during pregnancy to make room for your growing baby. Sadly, the 2 sides don’t always com back together afterwards.
👉🏼Here's a way to self-test it after 6 weeks postpartum.https://www.ourfitfamilylife.com/better-body-after-baby-program/

Can You Target Belly Fat (or any  specific fat area)?
I wish I could say “Yes”…
Wouldn’t it be wonderful if we could lose fat in certain area and add some in other? 😜
The truth is: we can’t select where we lose (or gain!) fat.
.
🧐So what about all my core workouts and the inspirational transformation pictures from my students on @mommybodybliss ?! 
In just 6 weeks many of them lose inches around their waist and flatten their tummy, no one can dispute this. 
So what’s the difference?
.
✅Well, when you perform the right exercises and techniques, you can efficiently strengthen your inner core muscles naturally acting like a corset/girdle/Spanx for your abdomen. 
Hello to a narrower waist, flatter stomach, better posture, less back pain… 
Notice that I didn’t mention anything about “burning fat” or “losing weight”!
.
❗️There are no shortcuts:
If you combine the right core exercise & daily habits with good nutrition, not only will you feel awesome, you’ll soon transform your body and become fitter, stronger, healthier and leaner!
.
So, do my students lose weight with my postpartum programs? 
Some of them do lose weight because they create new healthy fitness + eating habits along the way, but some don’t lose a pound, yet still see and feel major changes 🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼
.
One of my students said: 
💌“Despite exercising & eating healthy I wasn’t seeing much progress. 
This program is exactly what I needed to learn how to reconnect with my core, abdominals & pelvic floor. 
I tried doing it on my own & this program put it all together for me. I am so grateful.”
~ Amanda
.
🔎Detailed instructions and step by step video tutorial for the abdominal breathing technique available only in my Programs, I go through each movement required to internally engage and strengthen your core in detail.
🌸The next Better Body after Baby program starts 🔜 on September 13th 
Limited spots 🌸

Of course I’m not breastfeeding in this picture, but when people see my kids drink from my running vest, they either smile, laugh, or try to look somewhere else, embarrassed or offended?! 
Proof that the taboo surrounding breastfeeding isn’t going away any time soon. 
Luckily I’ve never been asked to cover up these kind of teats though 😆

“I’ll restrengthen my core once I’m done having children”😬
While I’m a huge believer that “it’s never too late to make improvements”, I highly recommend restrengthening your core between pregnancies.
.
“Why?” you may ask! Why restrengthen a system, that is going to be weakened by 9 more months of pregnancy and another delivery and postpartum?
Here are few “why’s”
.
1️⃣Because we need a functional core to live back pain free and leak free during the few months or years in between pregnancies. It’s not about having a flat tummy or not - it’s about having a core that allows you to do your “Mommy job”, practice your favorite activities, or just daily tasks without feeling pain in your body.
2️⃣Because even if you don’t have any symptoms and if you don’t feel that your core has been impacted by your pregnancy... it has, and another pregnancy would additionally stress and impact your neglected core.
3️⃣Because the longer you ignore your core and issues, the longer it may take to reconnect and restrengthen everything. The key is to become aware and remain aware of the system. To feel how breathing, posture and movement work together.  I’m alway saddened to see women ending up with a prolapse after a few kids because no one told them about core restrengthening after having children. 
4️⃣Because research shows that suffering from pelvic floor dysfunction has an adverse effect on quality of life and self-confidence.
5️⃣Because we are postpartum forever, and if you don’t improve and maintain core function along with awareness, then you’ll be like Millions of other Moms just accepting that pelvic floor dysfunctions, diastasis recti, back aches, … are just part of the Motherhood package, when it really it does NOT have to be that way
.
The pelvic floor is part of a dynamic system that is strengthened through breathing, proper posture, form and regular abdominal breathing exercises! These exercises are examples of the type of moves I use daily to strengthen my core.
The key is to become aware of the system, strengthen it, and feel how it works to maintain core function before, during and after having children🙏🏼

You guys may have notice that I barely talk about weight loss.
❤️My goal is too help your improve core function, strength, posture, and overall habit, but I’m not here to tell you that you need to melt those extra pounds if you don’t want too! 
.
✅Abdominal breathing exercises are key to getting rid of the post-pregnancy pooch and restore core function 
➡️➡️➡️Our inner core muscles are stretched and weakened after having babies and restoring proper connection, tension, and strength is essential before getting back to your usual workouts and activities. 
❗️Don’t skip the steps. If your inner core is weak your whole body will struggle and you won’t be able to reach your fitness and flat tummy goals.
.
➡️Try 4 rounds with 8 reps per move.
Engage your PF and exhale fully on each rep. 
.
🌈I wanted to thank you all again for your sweet words in response to my previous post. So grateful for this community!
.
Online programs available at the link in my Bio
🔜The next Better Body after Baby session starts on September 13th 💕

Not the epic shot I was expecting but for some reason my passenger didn’t want to re-attempt it 😆
A few weeks ago this account reached 400k and I wanted to take a minute to acknowledge this new milestone and celebrate YOU 🎉
.
Each time you like, save, or share my posts you help me spread the word about pre & postnatal fitness! 
So thank you for being here, thank you for all your comments, emojis, and messages ❤️
.
At least 406,000 women know better how to care for their Mama bodies - how to prevent or improve core issues - how to feel more confident in and about their bodies.
.
I created this account 7 years ago, and this is just the beginning ✨
So stay tuned, there’s so much more to share! 😘

If you’ve only got 15 minutes, minimal space, and nothing but your Mama Body to work with, you don’t have to choose between lower body strength training and cardio! 
You can have both 🙌🏼
.
This quick [but intense] workout will kick you butt!
➡️Try 2 rounds with 1 minute for each move.
🔥Feel free to add short breaks in between exercises or rounds, and shake those legs!
📌Save this workout and the next time you do it, take fewer or shorter breaks! 
It gives you something to work towards 💪🏼
.
Let me know how you like it!
.
🌸Programs available for EVERY stage of motherhood on my website🌸
Click the link in Bio for more info

Here are 4️⃣ mobility exercises that target hips, rib cage, shoulders, and spine!
.
Save this routine for later, you’ll need it!
➡️Try 2 rounds with 1 minute per move.
It will take you just 12 minutes of well a deserved self-care 🥰
.
Slouching is a common posture issue for Moms (did you realize that we’re doing most things hunched over?).
➡️When your shoulders roll forward, a bunch of compensation happens up and down the chain:
💥Tight neck, 
💥Tight hip flexors
💥Weakened glutes…
.
Did you just catch yourself sitting up a little? 😜
Don’t feel bad if you were!
I was a lifelong athlete and considered myself in shape even before I became pregnant, however, I truly never knew about the demands of motherhood and the level of fatigue I could reach.
It’s HARD, but there’s nothing more powerful than learning what your body needs to function properly, and putting yourself at the top of the priority list!
.
❗️As moms we spend so much time taking care of everyone around us, but sometimes we neglect to take care of ourselves, especially our physical health. 
We don’t “have time”, we’re “too busy”,  we have “other priorities”, but if our bodies aren’t healthy, we can’t function optimally.
.
You DESERVE to feel your best! ✨
.
❤️Inspiring stories at @mommybodybliss 
❤️Online programs are available for every stage of Motherhood on my website.
Click the link in my Bio to choose yours

I always wonder when I’ll get used to being a “grown-up” 😆
I feel I’m the same as when I was in College, but with a “gown-up life”!
A family, a house, a small business, bills… but my brain can’t keep up.
Any chance I’m not alone feeling that way? 😅
.
Well, a lot of you have been asking why I didn’t organize a Summer session for my Better Body after Baby program.
This is why: I feel like I’ve been holding my breath “during Covid”, and now that things are getting back to normal (🤞🏼) I’m overwhelmed with everything.
.
Looking forward to seeing my parents next week so I can take a little break from parenting and grown up life!
Stay tuned though! Even if I’m all or nothing with this app, I’ll try to pop up more in your feed.
I have so much to share about postnatal fitness with you ❤️
.
Feel free to share your own tips below on how to stay afloat with adulthood this summer.
Take care all!

DO YOU REALLY NEED TO WAIT 6 WEEKS? 🔍
One of the most common questions I receive is “When is it safe to return to exercise after childbirth?”
.
Well, it depends what you mean by “exercise”. 
➡️Specific exercises can be very beneficial to help your body recover right after childbirth, regardless of the way you gave birth ✨
.
Of course, I’m not talking about exercises like running, jumping jacks, front planks or burpees 😉
Very gentle exercises based on abdominal breathing are hugely beneficial to awaken your core and pelvic floor muscles safely
to progressively regain your strength, recover quickly, and properly.
.
❤️I can guide you on the road to help your body heal and avoid the common mistakes too many new Moms make when they resume exercise after baby.
.
Let’s heal your core with a strategy and care 🙌🏼
.
🌸1st, 2nd and 3rd weeks PP:
RE-CONNECT your inner core
.
🌸4th, 5th and 6th weeks PP:
RE-ACTIVATE your deepest ab muscles safely
.
🌸7th and 8th weeks PP:
RE-STRENGTHEN your whole core!
.
In my Immediate Postpartum program, each phase comes with specific breathing technique tutorials and gentle inner core exercises.
You’ll also discover new (breast)feeding stretches to alleviate common upper back pain, improve rounded shoulders and tight chest muscles 🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼
.
Let’s kickstart your recovery safely!
More info about the immediate postpartum period in my stories ❤️

node.text:
When should you think about your pelvic floor and breath during your workout? 🧐
Always? Never? Sometimes?
.
➡️Well, one of the goals of a core rehab program is to restore the natural pelvic floor reflex (where your pelvic floor responds automatically, without you having to think of it)
It takes mindful practice, time, and consistency, but most of us can get there✨
.
➡️So to answer the question, I would say that you should:
“ALWAYS” think of your pelvic floor and breath at the beginning of your core rehab journey.
Then you can work your way to “SOMETIMES” when you perform inner core focused workouts or new and/or more changing exercises.
.
✅Here’s a PROGRESSIVE STRATEGY:
1️⃣Reconnect the inner core components (especially the pelvic floor and diaphragm), 
2️⃣Learn how to coordinate them 
3️⃣Gradually use the breathing technique and strategies you developed in the activities you love.
🤩First, the core activation is conscious, and then it gradually becomes automatic!
.
❗️Note that during a workout like this one, I don’t use my abdominal breathing technique, but I always exhale on exertion.
This is a glute focused workout, but when using the right breathing technique every exercise can become an inner core exercise too, even when you don’t consciously think of your pelvic floor!
The Pelvic floor and diaphragm work together (I’ve linked a blog post about it in my stories)
.
🙏🏼I don’t take my healthy pelvic floor function for granted. It requires maintenance to continue to perform optimally. 
We’re postpartum forever!🥰
.
❤️Inspiring stories at @mommybodybliss 
❤️Online programs are available for every stage of Motherhood on my website. 
Click the link in my Bio to choose yours🪄

LOOSE SKIN •
For all of you who were wondering if I have loose skin from my 2 pregnancies… here it is! 😜
.
There was a time when I would have simply deleted this picture… but today seeing my loose skin doesn’t make me cringe! 
This pic just reminds me of the great time we had this weekend… and that I’m so freaking lucky to be a Mom!
This body expanded and shrank twice - giving life to my 2 wonderful boys 💙💙
.
➡️It’s time to accept that women don’t “bounce back” after having babies.
The societal expectation is that mothers need to get back to their previous shape - as if nothing had ever happened! 
Not only is this shaming and degrading, but it ignores the fact that SO MUCH has happened, and there’s no reason to be embarrassed about the way we look.
.
❤️Don’t let social media or anyone else shape the way you feel about your body!
Embrace yourself with all your flaws, and if you want to make changes, work toward them because you love your body, not because you hate it.
.
Even if our Mama bodies are different, it is possible to regain strength and function, and be happy with the way we look.
Be proud of what your body has accomplished ✨
.
Do you have loose skin of your own?
➡️Head to my Stories to read a few tips to show some love to your skin after pregnancy.
No magical tricks to tighten loose skin, but I really believe in the cumulative effect to make a great changes in the long term😘
i love to hear from you, so be sure to let me know what you think of them, and feel free too add your comments or own tips below ✨

DIATASIS RECTI - Post 7/7
Spanx, belly wraps & girdles?
.
Keep in mind that a Diastasis Recti is a result of overstretched connective tissue and muscles, so squeezing your abdomen won’t solve the problem. 
Healing Ab exercises are critical to restrengthen your deepest ab layer, aka your “natural corset”. 
If your inner core muscles are weak: your organs fall forward against the ab-midline, you’re also most likely to look/ feel bloated, giving you that “still pregnant” look.
👙No wrap/girdle/corset can do the job for you!
.
Your strengthened inner core muscles will do the job they are designed for, providing a built in corset you won’t have to take off.
.
More in my Stories.
I’ll soon talk about abdominal support for the immediate postpartum period (from birth to 8 weeks PP). I think devices like these can be effective as a temporary abdominal & lower back support in this specific window, as long as they don’t squish your tummy, prevent your from breathing properly, or using your abdomen!
.
❤️More transformations and testimonials at @mommybodybliss 
❤️Online programs available for every stage of Motherhood on my website. 
Click the link in my Bio to choose the one that’s right for you.
